g.text: This workflow demonstrates how to read multiple files using a loop. The files are
contained in a zip file (located in the meta node). They are then extracted into a temp
folder and the temp folder is indexed. The list of files is passed into the loop, which
reads one file at a time (all files have the same file structure, just different data) and
the output is concatenated in the loop end node.
This meta node creates a folder in
the temp space and puts a couple of
files into it. The flow variable
output denotes the path to this
